Patch Set 1:

This patch hides the shortcut from the toolbar control where Bold and Italic would still show shortcuts. Not sure what's better, or actually worse.

Patch Set 1:

Yes because the menubars are still using the other command:
https://opengrok.libreoffice.org/search?project=core&full=underlinesingle&defs=&refs=&path=&hist=&type=&xrd=&nn=1

Patch Set 1:

No... so toolbars use the complex uno:Underline that can be used to set any underline styles:

https://opengrok.libreoffice.org/search?project=core&full=%22uno%5C%3Aunderline%22&defs=&refs=&path=*xml&hist=&type=&xrd=&nn=1&si=path&si=path&n=25

while menu bars use the single / double underline commands which are for turning on/off two specific underline styles.

I start to think that things are fine and the bug is really a NAB.

Patch Set 1:

> I start to think that things are fine and the bug is really a NAB.

OTOH, the single click menu bar entry is more expected to be assigned to a shortcut than a complex toolbar widget. Making the patch a +2. How about routing .uno:Underline to .uno:UnderlineSingle via the target attribute? Maybe this takes the shortcut on both commands.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

Fine for me to push it.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> > I start to think that things are fine and the bug is really a NAB.

On the other hand I also sort of expect people to miss the Ctrl+U showing up on the toolbar button, like it always did, if this goes in.
Let me think a bit more on this.

I think the bug is NAB, it's better the current way
